					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Gordon on character balance again</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=127719" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/everquest_h.html">Forget Balance (Affirmative Action) I Want Equality</a><P>

I want the same down time, able to slay similar mob (Not always some being class specific is cool) at the same level with the same amount of risk (Again not always some risk being higher/lower due to class specific).<P>

Example 1: (Just made up numbers)<BR>
Necro kills a Tesch Gnoll down time until full mana 2 minutes.<BR>
Warrior Kills a Tesch Gnoll down time until full HP 2 minutes.<BR>
Mage Kills a Tesch Gnoll down time until full HP of pet and mana is 2 minutes.<P>

Example 2: (again just made up numbers)<BR>
Necro kills a Giant Skele down time until full mana 2 minutes. (Necro specialty)<BR>
Warrior Kills a Giant Skele down time until full HP 4 minutes.<BR>
Mage Kills a Giant Skele down time until full HP of pet and mana is 4 minutes.<P>

Every class should be equal (except for specialties)
not the SAME!!!<P>

<B>Though I do thank your for taking the time to post your opinion, balance is not about equality. It's not about making everyone able to do the same thing in the same time with the same amount of risk.<P>
 
The equality that you suggest is incompatible with the concept of a class-based system with class-interdependence. There are a few games out there that support class-less system which you may find more to your liking.<P> 

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=127719">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

